5:
Colonel Selene! Do you not
understand the implication of your
actions?
6:
You are in serious violation of Navy
code!
8:
Would you rather I had let that
whole float slip into the Maw?
10:
Do not change the topic, Colonel.
We are here to discuss how you
mobilized forces for personal use.
Your FLAGRANT abuse of power.
11:
And your fleet contained not only
Navy vessels, but civilian crafts
and—get this—pirate ships!
14:
I'd heard our sailors were there as
the result of some kind of
misunderstanding. Sloppy orders,
perhaps?
17:
Watch your attitude, Colonel. This
isn't like you.
19: Not like me? You have to be joking.
22:
I know you've already decided on
my sentence. I know this whole trial
is nothing more than a set-up!
24:
Before you send me away, let me
give you some free advice. There's a
storm brewing. And you're right in its
path.
26:
But you already knew that, didn't
you? You're just too scared to face
facts, so you try to distract yourself
with this cute theater production.
29:
Stop hiding! Fight! It's either that, or
sink like a stone.
32:
Colonel Selene. The jury has
reached a verdict. You are to be
divested of all your rights as a
commander until further notice.
34:
You will hold authority over one ship
and one ship alone. Let this be a
lesson to you.
38:
I got what I deserved. But the real
issue is the powers-that-be are
disciplining their cat for knocking
over a few vases when the whole
world is about to crumble.
39:
Desperate times call for desperate
measures. If this doesn't get through
to them, I don't know what will.
42: I'm guessing... you got in trouble?
54:
Wouldn't mind a shoulder to cry on
for the night. Especially if its yours.
60:
Selene, I came to tell you we're
surrounded by pirates.
65:
Well, that was faster than expected.
They've got a sharper nose for blood
than sharks.
68:
There's at least twenty ships. Are you
gonna fight them?
71:
Of course. I was the one who invited
them to this tango.
73:
Remember how I asked you to pitch
in?
80:
Heh-heh-heh. Never thought I'd find
the Steel Wolf without 'er pack.
82:
We hunt 'er down and the Navy's just
a bunch o' sittin' ducks. We're in for
some smooth sailin', me hearties!
85:
It's a two-fer-one deal! We take 'er
'ead AND that float!
95:
Ma'am, we're running low on ammo.
Do we bring out the bayonets?
99:
No. Roll my pet out. I'm going for a
ride.
102:
This will probably be my last fight as
the Steel Wolf.
104:
You have all served me well. Thank
you.
107:
The next time we meet, we meet as
equals!
115:
Arr... Just what is that ship made of?
It's unnatural, I tell ye!
116:
They've stopped rainin' cannonballs
down on us, Cap'n. This is our
chance!
117:
If we can board 'em, this battle's
ours. They've got fancy guns, but
we've got dozens of swords. Full
speed ahead, you bilge rats!
119:
A tank?! You're gonna send us all
down to Davy Jones' locker!
122:
Exactly. Sorry, but this was the only
thing I could think of!
128:
That might've been... more
excitement than I could handle...
131:
You're awake! I was half-afraid we
wouldn't make it!
134:
Sorry. I got a little caught up.
Wanted to bring down as many
pirates as possible.
135: So, how are things on the surface?
139:
The captain went down with his ship.
The rest of the pirates ran when the
Navy arrived.
140:
Come to think of it, didn't they take
away your command and that iron
cruiser?
144:
On paper, yes. But my sailors won't
be breaking any more laws for my
sake.
147:
Alk. Is there a place for me in
Starview Village?
151:
Always, but... are you fine with just
leaving?
156:
Yeah. Figured it'd be best if I joined
you in playing dead.
157:
I've already built a network that
stretches all four corners of this sea.
159:
The next step is going interstellar.
Doesn't that sound like a blast?
164:
I, uh... don't really get military stuff.
But I'm sure you'll do great, Selene.
168:
What are you talking about? You're
my right-hand man now.
169:
Well, let's not keep Starview waiting.
Oh, and just a warning, I'm VERY
particular about my décor. If my
bed isn't at least the size of a small
yacht, I won't sleep in it.
172:
What? Why does it need to be that
big?
179:
Actually... never mind. I, uh... respect
your privacy and wouldn't want to
intrude...
188: WHY WOULD YOU TELL ME THAT?
